<BlogPost title="Welcome to Our New Home on the Web" date="2026-03-15" author="Yogesh Adhikari" slug="welcome-to-bmgr">
  <p>For a while now, BMGR has existed in group chats, in community halls, and in the memories of people who've attended our events. But we never had a place online that felt like <em>ours</em> — somewhere people could visit and understand who we are, what we do, and why it matters.</p>
  <p>This website changes that.</p>
  <p>When I started working on this project, I wanted it to reflect what makes us different. We're not just another music group. We are Bhutanese Nepalis — people who carry a specific history, a specific sound, and a specific way of coming together through music. Our songs are rooted in the hills of Bhutan and the plains of Jhapa. Our instruments — the harmonium, the madal, the tabla — are the same ones our parents played. That identity is what this website is built around.</p>
  <p>Here's what you'll find:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 pl-2">
    <li><strong>Members</strong> — profiles of all 13 active members, with bios and instruments</li>
    <li><strong>Events</strong> — upcoming programs, song repertoire, and equipment</li>
    <li><strong>Gallery</strong> — photos from concerts, rehearsals, Deusi-Bhailo, and community events</li>
    <li><strong>Blog</strong> — stories, recaps, and updates written by our members</li>
    <li><strong>Contact</strong> — a simple way to reach us</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Everything on this site comes from real conversations with our members. Nothing here is filler. It's all us.</p>
  <p>We're also working toward some big milestones: official nonprofit registration, a grand summer concert in June 2026, and youth music programs to get our kids involved. This website will be the place to follow all of that.</p>
  <p>If you've been to one of our events, you already know what BMGR feels like. If you haven't — I hope this site gives you a reason to come find out.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-earth-faint">— Yogesh Adhikari<br />Operations & Technology, BMGR</p>
</BlogPost>
